Welcome to unchained API documentation

API Endpoints
Development Server:
http://127.0.0.1:4010/graphql

Main methods to getch assortments

Queries

assortment

get assortment by it's ID or slug

assortmentId:
string

(no description)

slug:
string

(no description)

Example

Request Content-Types: application/json
Query
query assortment($assortmentId: ID, $slug: String){
  assortment(assortmentId: $assortmentId, slug: $slug){
    _id
    created
    updated
    isActive
    isBase
    isRoot
    sequence
    tags
    meta
    texts(forceLocale: $forceLocale){
      _id
      locale
      slug
      title
      subtitle
      description
    }
    productAssignments
    filterAssignments
    linkedAssortments
    assortmentPaths
    children
  }
}
Variables
{
  "assortmentId": "string",
  "slug": "string"
}
Try it now
200 OK

Successful operation

type
Assortment
Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "data": {
    "assortment": {
      "_id": "string",
      "isActive": "boolean",
      "isBase": "boolean",
      "isRoot": "boolean",
      "sequence": "integer",
      "tags": [
        "string"
      ],
      "texts": {
        "_id": "string",
        "locale": "string",
        "slug": "string",
        "title": "string",
        "subtitle": "string",
        "description": "string"
      }
    }
  }
}

me

Query
query me{

    _id
    email
    username
    isEmailVerified
    isGuest
    isInitialPassword
    name
    emails
    roles
    tags
    orders(includeCarts: $includeCarts)
    quotations
    logs(offset: $offset, limit: $limit)
    bookmarks
    paymentCredentials
    subscriptions
  }
}

Queries

order

Get a specific single order, use the otp to get access to the information without beeing logged in as the user that created the order

orderId:
string

(no description)

otp:
string

(no description)

Example

Request Content-Types: application/json
Query
query order($orderId: ID!, $otp: String){
  order(orderId: $orderId, otp: $otp){
    _id
    status
    created
    updated
    ordered
    orderNumber
    confirmed
    fullfilled
    meta
    items
    discounts
    documents(type: $type)
    supportedDeliveryProviders
    supportedPaymentProviders
    logs(limit: $limit, offset: $offset)
  }
}
Variables
{
  "orderId": "string",
  "otp": "string"
}
Try it now
200 OK

Successful operation

type
Order
Response Content-Types: application/json
Response Example (200 OK) 
{
  "data": {
    "order": {
      "_id": "string",
      "orderNumber": "string"
    }
  }
}

ID: object

The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

Example
object

Int: number

The Int scalar type represents non-fractional signed whole numeric values. Int can represent values between -(2^31) and 2^31 - 1.

Example
number

String: string

The String scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.

Work: object

_id:
ID
started:
Date

Timestamp when this work was allocated -> Locked for other workers

finished:
Date
created:
Date
updated:
Date
deleted:
Date
priority:
Int
type:
WorkType
status:
WorkStatus

Status is derived from the other fields. E.g. Work without started field has status NEW

worker:
String
input:
JSON
result:
JSON
error:
JSON

Work can have errors recorded, but nonetheless be marked as success

success:
Boolean
scheduled:
Date

If set, the work will not be allocated before this date

original:
Work

Link to original work: For retries, clones, ...

retries:
Int

How many times this work should be retried. A retried work is a clone with retries = parent.retries - 1 usually. Plugins can implement different workflows.

timeout:
Int

If work is ALLOCATED longer than timeout it is considered as FAILED and could be cleaned.

Example
{
  "_id": "object",
  "started": "object",
  "finished": "object",
  "created": "object",
  "updated": "object",
  "deleted": "object",
  "priority": "number",
  "type": "string",
  "status": "string",
  "worker": "string",
  "input": "object",
  "result": "object",
  "error": "object",
  "success": "boolean",
  "scheduled": "object",
  "original": {
    "_id": "object",
    "started": "object",
    "finished": "object",
    "created": "object",
    "updated": "object",
    "deleted": "object",
    "priority": "number",
    "type": "string",
    "status": "string",
    "worker": "string",
    "input": "object",
    "result": "object",
    "error": "object",
    "success": "boolean",
    "scheduled": "object",
    "original": {
      "_id": "object",
      "started": "object",
      "finished": "object",
      "created": "object",
      "updated": "object",
      "deleted": "object",
      "priority": "number",
